Carotid-cavernous sinus fistula associated with a primitive trigeminal artery.
 Carotid-cavernous sinus fistulas are not rare, but they have never been reported in association with persistent primitive trigeminal artery.
 We recently encountered such a case.
 The Jaeger-Hamby procedure was employed, with mandatory occlusion of the primitive trigeminal artery.
